@wdduncan Looks like this branch is running fine locally (with Python 3.7.3) and on Travis (with Python 3.7.1).

Perhaps the above error has to do with your local environment?

Either way - the bug is originating from a dependency that Tox needs.

@dehays we are merging this. This makes the schema less generic and models the mixs properties directly in the schema. This makes certain things clearer as there is no longer a '2-level' schema. The downside is that we introduce a sync issue but we are developing tools to make this easier.

This will make the schema more like:
